'''Kristi de Vries''' (born [[March 26]], [[1982]] in [[Fontana, California]], [[United States]]) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[softball]] player, who represents the [[Netherlands women's national softball team|Dutch national team]] in international competitions.<ref name="bio">[http://results.beijing2008.cn/WRM/ENG/BIO/Athlete/0/218240.shtml Athlete biography: Kristi de Vries], beijing2008.cn, ret: Aug 16, 2008</ref>

De Vries played for [[Crunch (softball)|Crunch]], [[Gordon's Panthers]], [[Ohio State University]] and since 2005 for [[Sparks Haarlem]]. She is a [[pitcher]] and [[first baseman]] who bats and throws right-handed. She competes for the Dutch national team since 2003. In 2003 and 2004 she was the best pitcher of the Ohio State University. She is part of the Dutch team for the [[2008 Summer Olympics]] in [[Beijing]].<ref name="bio"/>

